def: Inscribed with a posy.In poised lockets bribe the fair. Gay.
Of, pertaining to, or obtained from, sandalwood (Santalum); --used specifically to designate an acid obtained as a resinous or redcrystalline dyestuff, which is called also santalin.
To raise little bladders or blisters upon; to inflame andseparate the cuticle of; to blister. Wiseman.
A prefix signifying over, above, beyond, upon.
A roof having a rounded form, hemispherical or nearly so; also,a celing having the same form. When on a large scale it is usuallycalled dome.
The quality of being inconceivable; inconceivableness.The inconceivability of the Infinite. Mansel.
One who uses his tongue; a talker; a story-teller; a gossip.[Poetic.]Step by step we rose to greatness; through the tonguesters we mayfall. Tennyson.
Having a fringe of feathers, as the legs of certian birds; orof hairs, as the legs of a setter dog.
The saury pike; -- called also gofnick.
A servile or hypocritical flatterer. Carlyle.
